_source\": \"Substory conclusions: S1 (C-slot) + S2 (C-slot) + S3 (C-slot) + S4 (C-slot) + S5 (C-slot); narrative/00_throughline.md; REPORT.md §Future directions\"\n  },\n  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"The OM proteome replication is the immediate near-term experiment — the data provider already has it slated for summer 2026, and it nails down the two post-hoc findings (lptC2 transcript-protein decoupling and Pal-Tol induction) before publication. The SigU regulon characterization is the longer novel arc: no Caulobacter SigU regulon exists in the literature, and the late ChvI cohort from NB03 gives us a ready candidate target list to validate.\\n\\n**Sources:** Substory conclusions: S1 (C-slot) + S2 (C-slot) + S3 (C-slot) + S4 (C-slot) + S5 (C-slot); narrative/00_throughline.md; REPORT.md §Future directions\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Future directions\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Key Findings\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"CO001\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"content_overflow\",\n      \"summary\": \"Shortened unified_point from 336 to 113 chars to satisfy content_overflow P1 (G.10-C slot_kind=title, deck_close); dropped rhetorical opener 'A single envelope catastrophe — lipid A loss —' and qualifiers 'partially independent' and 'together' (all preserved verbatim in key_takeaways and speaker_notes_seed); substantive claim — five adaptive layers explaining how and why Caulobacter alone tolerates the deletion — preserved intact.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
